{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-doc-template-js","path":"/docs/installing/installing-appsody/","webpackCompilationHash":"58b38ab8b4fff6689b63","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"installing-appsody\"><a href=\"#installing-appsody\" aria-label=\"installing appsody permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installing Appsody</h1>\n<p>The easiest way to install Appsody is to use the installers, which are available for all supported platforms, except Windows®.</p>\n<h2 id=\"platforms\"><a href=\"#platforms\" aria-label=\"platforms permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Platforms</h2>\n<p>Appsody supports the following operating systems on x86 hardware:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>macOS®</li>\n<li>Ubuntu</li>\n<li>Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL)</li>\n<li>Windows® - Windows 10 Professional and Windows 10 Enterprise editions only</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"requirements\"><a href=\"#requirements\" aria-label=\"requirements permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Requirements</h2>\n<p>To use all of Appsody's functions, you need to install <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/get-started/\">Docker</a> and start the Docker daemon on your system. </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Currently, Appsody supports using a local Docker daemon only. See the <a href=\"/docs/faq/#13-can-i-use-the-minikube-docker-daemon-for-development\">FAQ</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In environments where Docker is not available, a subset of Appsody commands can be used with Buildah as detailed in the <a href=\"/docs/faq#9-can-i-use-appsody-without-docker\">FAQ</a>. Prerequisites specific to each operating system are provided within the links of the following section.</p>\n<h2 id=\"using-installers\"><a href=\"#using-installers\" aria-label=\"using installers permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using installers</h2>\n<p>Installation steps are covered in the following sections:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/installing/macos\">Installing on macOS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/installing/rhel\">Installing on RHEL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/installing/ubuntu\">Installing on Ubuntu</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Appsody does not have an installer package for Windows, so to install Appsody on that operating system follow:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/installing/windows\">Installing on Windows</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"alternative-install-methods\"><a href=\"#alternative-install-methods\" aria-label=\"alternative install methods permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Alternative install methods</h2>\n<h3 id=\"appsody-binaries\"><a href=\"#appsody-binaries\" aria-label=\"appsody binaries permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Appsody binaries</h3>\n<p>If you prefer not to use an installer, you can install Appsody by using a binary file. These instructions are for installing on macOS, Ubuntu, and RHEL. For Windows, follow <a href=\"/docs/installing/windows\">Installing on Windows</a>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Go to the <a href=\"https://github.com/appsody/appsody/releases\">Appsody Releases page</a>, scroll to the release you want and download the file that is appropriate to your operating system. For example, on macOS: <code>appsody_v.r.m-darwin-amd64.tar.gz</code>, where <code>v.r.m</code> indicates the release tag.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Extract the files by running:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code>tar -xvf appsody_v.r.m-darwin-amd64.tar.gz\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>This is a nested zip file so if you use a GUI you might have to unzip twice.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"building-appsody-from-source\"><a href=\"#building-appsody-from-source\" aria-label=\"building appsody from source permalink\" class=\"header-link-icon\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Building Appsody from source</h3>\n<p>If you would like to build Appsody from the source code, look at <a href=\"https://github.com/appsody/appsody/blob/master/build.md\">Building from Source</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Overview - Installing Appsody"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"pagePath":"/docs/installing/installing-appsody/"}}}